      "solution": "w, h = map(int, input().split())\nfill = input()\nempty = input()\nif h > 1 and h % 2 == 1 and w > 0:\n    for i in range(h):\n        flip = True\n        line = \"\"\n        for j in range(w):\n            y = (j-h//2) % (h-1)\n            flip = [flip, not flip][y == 0]\n            y = [y, h-y-1][flip]\n            line += [empty, fill][y == i]\n        print(line)\nelif h == 1 and w > 0:\n    print(fill*w)\nelse:\n    print(\"Invalid Input\")\n",
      "statement": "The goal is to draw a triangle wave in a 2d graph, given that [[h]] is the height of the graph and [[w]] defines the horizontal range of the graph.\n\nThe wave should start from the middle left and proceed diagonally up to the top of the graph, then diagonally down, etc.\n<<Note:>>  amplitude = ([[h]]-1) / 2\n\nThe following rules should be applied:\n  1- [[h]] must be odd \n  2- [[w]] and [[h]] should be at least 1\nIf either rule is broken output should be: {{Invalid Input}}",
